{"title": "Bethink Yourselves!", "description": "As Russia goes to war against Japan, Tolstoy urges those at all levels of society, from the Tsar down to the common soldier, to consider their actions in the light of Christ's teaching. \"However strange this may appear, the most effective and certain deliverance of men from all the calamities which they inflict upon themselves and from the most dreadful of all\u2014war\u2014is attainable, not by any external general measures, but merely by that simple appeal to the consciousness of each separate man which, nineteen hundred years ago, was proposed by Jesus\u2014that every man bethink himself, and ask himself, who is he, why he lives, and what he should and should not do.\" (Introduction by David Barnes, and extract from Chapter VI)", "duration": 6106, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "217", "name": "Leo Tolstoy"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt18/bethink_yourselves_1205.jpg", "copyright_year": "1904", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Philosophy", "Political Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "David Barnes"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Barnes"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Nadine Eckert-Boulet"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Diana Majlinger"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bethink_yourselves_db_librivox/bethinkyourselves_01_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 391}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bethink_yourselves_db_librivox/bethinkyourselves_02_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 450}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bethink_yourselves_db_librivox/bethinkyourselves_03_tolstoy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 380}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV", "readers": [94], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/bethink_yourselves_db_librivox/be